history.content:
If you have a conflicting class, then the system will never enroll you off of the waitlist.

You could try following the instructions in @5173.

Hi, I'm an undeclared sophomore in L&S. I'm currently taking CS 61B and have taken 61A and 70, so I will be able to declare at the end of the semester. For Phase 1 enrollment, I attempted to do CS 61C and CS 170. Since I'm still undeclared, I'm on the wait list for CS 170.

Is there anything I can do to get off the wait list faster, or can I only wait until the end of Phase 2? Also, will I be able to make it off the wait list at all, given that 61C has conflicting times with 170?
history.subject: CS 170 : getting off wait list?
